	<scenario>
		<description>This scenario puts a fleet of Warthogs in the skies of San Francisco Bay near the San Francisco International Airport (KSFO).

The fleet starts just east of the airport and proceeds on a northerly heading at 1300 feet AGL.  If you take off runway 1R or 1L, climb to 300 feet and turn right to heading 90.  In front of you will be the contrails of several Warthogs moving in a generally easterly direction through the hills.

To aid visibility, by default the planes leave a contrail.  Without contrail the planes are nearly impossible to spot until you are right on top of them.

The Warthogs are air-to-air targets, you can damage them with heavy guns, machine guns, or (if you can hit them!) heavy bombs.
  
When you shoot or bomb the Warthogs they will catch fire, slow down, fall, and finally crash (to see the smoke and fire you must have Particles enabled in View/Rendering Options).

To damage the Warthogs takes one or more direct hits from a machine gun or heavy gun, or a close strike by a heavy bomb.   The Warthogs are fairly robust targets--similar to a tank in difficulty to kill.

Install this scenario in the FlightGear/data/AI directory.

Any aircraft that shoots guns or drops bombs can damage the Warthogs.  The Fairchild A-10 Thunderbolt is a great choice - http://wiki.flightgear.org/index.php/Fairchild_A-10
		</description>
		
